T6. Kimboza Forest Reserve c. 48 -50 km Morogoro to Matombo road. Lowland evergreen rain forest on dolomitic marble traversed by permanent streams (Kimboza and Ruvu). Dominant trees include barkia filicoidea, khaya myasica, Chlorophora excelsa, Drypetes, Aningeria and Sterculia appediculata. Introduced trees include Cedrella and tectona. Dominant lianes are Saba florida, Hippocratea and rhoicissus.
